As you may have seen with the wooden fluid pipes, the water seems like it is almost sloshing around. This is not the case, the pipes actually move around the liquid, as they think it is mouthwash, but are not smart enough to tell the difference between the fluids.

Luckily, you can stop thier stupidity with a wrench and crouching, with toggling input on/off u can make the pipes work more effeciently and remove sloshing. (Make sure you do this the correct way and not have water going to the source instead of going away from the source). Just play around with that toy wrench I gave you a few quests ago.

Oh and one last thing. Pipes don't like burning thier tongue while sloshing. Each material of a pipe has a different heat tolerance. Make sure you never go over the heat tolerence with the fluid you want to move around, you really don't want to burn the pipes tongue );

